Enrichment Analysis of H3K27ac peaks (enhancer)

last changed: 2023-08-29

Annotation of H3K27ac peaks to enhancers

Load data

To annotate the peaks to the corresponding enhacner regions/genes the list with all peaks is required as well as a list containing all enhancer target genes and regions. The annotation list was then filtered for only high scoring targets.

Find enhancer regions and annotate gene IDs

Next, these list were used to find the corresponding enhancers using the first list (GH.region) with the function findOverlaps. Then the target genes were annotated using the second list (GH.anno.elite).

> enhcr.H3ac <- peaks
> 
> for (x in 1:4) {
+   curr.peaks <- peaks[[x]]
+   hits <- findOverlaps(curr.peaks, subject = GH.region)
+   overlap.H3ac <- peaks[[x]][hits@from, ]
+   mcols(overlap.H3ac)$GHid <- mcols(GH.region[hits@to, "name"])
+   df.over <- as.data.frame(overlap.H3ac)
+   mcols(overlap.H3ac)$symbol <- NA
+   ind <- intersect(df.over$name, GH.anno.elite$GHid)
+   mcols(overlap.H3ac)[which(df.over$name %in% ind), "symbol"] <- 
+     GH.anno.elite[which(GH.anno.elite$GHid %in% ind), "symbol"]
+   mcols(overlap.H3ac)[which(df.over$name %in% ind), "score"] <- 
+     GH.anno.elite[which(GH.anno.elite$GHid %in% ind), "combined_score"]
+   enhcr.H3ac[[x]] <- overlap.H3ac
+ }
> 
> saveRDS(enhcr.H3ac, "./Data/Enhancer2gene.rds")
> 
> head(enhcr.H3ac)

Since ENTREZ IDs are required to perform the enrichment analysis these were added taking the gene symbols with the function bitr:

> enhcr.ENTREZ <- lapply(enhcr.H3ac, function(n) {
+   bitr(n@elementMetadata$symbol, 
+        fromType="SYMBOL", 
+        toType="ENTREZID", 
+        OrgDb="org.Hs.eg.db")
+ })
>

Enrichment analysis of H3K27ac enhancer peaks

Reactome Pathway enrichment analysis

Finally, the filtered list with the coding genes can be used for an enrichment analysis using the function enrichPathway, which can be plotted using dotplot.

> # Reactome Enrichment:
> names(enhcr.ENTREZ) <- 1:4 %>% as.character()
> genes <- lapply(enhcr.ENTREZ, function(i) as.data.frame(i)$ENTREZID)
> 
> PA.enhcr <- compareCluster(geneCluster = genes,
+                            fun = "enrichPathway",
+                            pvalueCutoff = 0.05,
+                            pAdjustMethod = "BH")
> 
> PA.enhcr %>% as.data.frame() %>% paged_table()
> dotplot(PA.enhcr, 
+         showCategory = 10, 
+         title = "Reactome Pathway Enrichment Analysis (Enhancer)")

Gene Ontology enrichment analysis

Exactly the same as above can be done with the function enrichGO.

> # GO Enrichment:
> GO.enhcr <- compareCluster(geneCluster = genes,
+                            fun = "enrichGO",
+                            OrgDb = org.Hs.eg.db,
+                            ont = "BP",
+                            readable = T,
+                            pvalueCutoff = 0.05,
+                            pAdjustMethod = "BH")
> 
> GO.enhcr %>% as.data.frame() %>% paged_table()
> dotplot(GO.enhcr, 
+         showCategory = 10, 
+         title = "Gene Ontology Enrichment Analysis (Enhancer)")
